

Question 1
Suggest an appropriate software stack (operating system, web server, database server and programming runtime) for hosting ASP.NET web applications.

Answer (EN):
Operating System: Windows Server
Web Server: IIS
Database Server: SQL Server
Programming Runtime: .NET (ASP.NET)

答案（中）：
操作系统：Windows Server
Web 服务器：IIS
数据库服务器：SQL Server
运行环境：.NET (ASP.NET)

Question 2
Discuss the advantages of using the ASP.NET platform for developing web applications from the following aspects: Existing software environment, Customer support, Expandability and scalability, Rich and unified frameworks, Consistent software components.

Answer (EN):
Existing software environment: Many companies use Windows-based systems; easier to deploy ASP.NET
Customer support: Proprietary software offers support as part of the license
Expandability and scalability: Enterprise-grade architecture, supports future growth
Rich and unified frameworks: Supports MVC, Web API, SignalR, Razor Pages, Blazor, etc.
Consistent software components: Tools integrate well (Visual Studio, IIS, SQL Server, Windows Server)

答案（中）：
现有软件环境：Windows 系统已广泛使用，部署 ASP.NET 更方便
客户支持：商业软件包含技术支持
可扩展性与伸缩性：企业级架构，支持未来增长
丰富统一的框架：MVC、Web API、SignalR、Razor Pages、Blazor 等
一致的软件组件：Visual Studio、IIS、SQL Server、Windows Server 高度集成

Question 3
Identify and discuss the role of the 3 core components of MVC web architecture. Provide 2 examples for each.

Answer (EN):
Model: Handles data & business logic; examples: Product, Student
View: Handles UI & presentation; examples: Index.cshtml, Create.cshtml
Controller: Handles requests & coordinates Model/View; examples: HomeController, StudentController

答案（中）：
Model（模型）：处理数据和业务逻辑；例子：Product、Student
View（视图）：处理界面显示；例子：Index.cshtml、Create.cshtml
Controller（控制器）：处理请求并协调模型与视图；例子：HomeController、StudentController

Question 4
Discuss the advantages of MVC web architecture from the following aspects: Separation of concerns, Task distribution, Maintainability, Reusable, Unit Testable.

Answer (EN):
Separation of concerns: Components have specific responsibilities
Task distribution: Developers → Controller, Designers → View, DB Admins → Model
Maintainability: Changing one component minimally affects others
Reusable: Components can be reused in other projects
Unit Testable: Logic decoupled, easier automated testing

答案（中）：
关注点分离：组件职责明确
任务分工：开发→Controller，设计→View，DB 管理员→Model
可维护性：修改某组件影响小
可重用性：组件可用于其他项目
可单元测试：逻辑分离，便于自动测试

Question 5
Discuss how MVC web architecture helps in task distribution for a project team.

Answer (EN):
MVC allows developers, designers, and DB administrators to work independently on their components, improving efficiency and reducing conflicts.

答案（中）：
MVC 允许开发人员、设计师和数据库管理员各自负责不同组件，能够并行开发，提高团队效率并减少冲突。

Question 6
Discuss why URL routing is necessary for ASP.NET MVC web applications.

Answer (EN):
URL routing maps URLs to the correct controller and action because web pages are not physical files, enabling clean and flexible URLs.

答案（中）：
URL 路由用于将请求的 URL 映射到对应的控制器与动作方法，由于 MVC 网页不是实体文件，因此路由机制可实现清晰且灵活的 URL 结构。

Question 7
Discuss in words how the following URL is mapped:
https://www.abc.com/Product/Update/P001?quantity=123

Answer (EN):
Controller: ProductController
Action: Update
Parameter id: P001
Parameter quantity: 123

答案（中）：
该 URL 会映射到 ProductController 中的 Update 动作方法，其中 P001 作为 id 参数传入，而 quantity 的值为 123。

Question 8
Write the URL to access the following controller and action method. Pass S001 for id and 2024 for year.

public class StudentController : Controller {
  public IActionResult Detail(string id, int year) { ... }
}


Answer (EN):
https://www.abc.com/Student/Detail/S001?year=2024

答案（中）：
https://www.abc.com/Student/Detail/S001?year=2024

Question 9
Rewrite the code to map to the URL: https://www.abc.com/Product/Update/P001?quantity=123

Answer (EN / 中):

public class ProductController : Controller {
  public IActionResult Update(string id, int quantity) { ... }
}
